---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="About Austin Band | Belvedere Decks, Owner-Operated Maryland Deck Builder"
  description="Belvedere Decks is Austin Band's owner-operated deck company serving Maryland from Montgomery County with transparent pricing, honest inspections, and a 10-year written workmanship warranty."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">About us</p>
      <h1>A belvedere is a structure built to enjoy a beautiful view.</h1>
      <div class="rule"></div>
      <p class="lead">
        That's what a deck is for, and it's the standard every project here has to meet.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <!-- TODO: PHOTO - Austin on a finished deck, phone camera is fine. -->
      <h2 style="margin-top: 0;">I'm Austin Band, and Belvedere Decks is my company.</h2>
      <p>
        I live in Potomac and build across Maryland. Most of my work is in Montgomery
        County, from the Kentlands to Olney, Bethesda to Clarksburg. I've spent the last
        five years building decks professionally, and a lifetime before that working
        outside on our own home. That is why I run projects the way I'd want them run
        on my own house: the price built in front of you, the inspection narrated out
        loud, and the corners nobody can see treated like the ones everybody can.
      </p>

      <h2>How I run this company</h2>
      <p>
        When you call, you get me: the same person who measures your deck, prices it on
        the iPad in front of you the same visit, and stands behind the work for the next
        ten years in writing. I'll walk your existing deck with you and tell you what I
        find, good and bad: which posts are solid, whether water has gotten in where the
        deck meets your house, whether your frame can take new boards. If the honest
        answer is that you only need half the project you called about, that's the
        answer you'll get. Owner-operated is slower to scale, and better to hire.
      </p>

      <h2>What every project includes</h2>
      <ul class="checklist">
        <li>An exact price presented in person: same visit for resurfacing projects. Certain new builds and full facelifts can often be priced on-site during that first visit too, though we can't guarantee it for every project</li>
        <li>Three versions of your project, with the same code-perfect structure under all three</li>
        <li>Premium TimberTech and Trex boards, entry to architectural grade</li>
        <li>Permits and inspections handled where required</li>
        <li>A 10-year written workmanship warranty, on top of 25–50-year manufacturer board warranties</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Where we work</h2>
      <p>
        Anywhere in Maryland we can serve well. Most of our work is in Montgomery
        County (Potomac, North Potomac and the Kentlands, Bethesda, Olney, Boyds, and
        Clarksburg), but if you're elsewhere in the state, call: if we can get to you,
        we'll build for you.
      </p>
      <p>
        The first step costs nothing: an honest look at your deck and an exact price,
        same visit, no obligation.
      </p>
      <p><a class="btn primary" href="/estimate">Get a Free Estimate</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
